WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Eclairium' originated from the observation of lightning on one
stormy day, then, I said to myself: "Hey, I could make a game with
this!"... and so it came...

  The general idea of this Workbench game is to use lightning to
eliminate tiles that contain various coloured shapes. But as
lightning is somewhat random and unpredictable; you never know
where it will fall... in this case one known fact is, like normal
natural lightning bolts: they will go toward the ground.

  To complicate matters, as the game progress, 'indestructible'
tiles may appear and sometimes, some clouds (which are used to
send lightning bolts) may disappear.

  Every time a lightning bolt is sent and no tiles are eliminated,
a number of tiles will randomly appear on the board. That number
of tiles will double, until at least one tile is eliminated.
Better watch out that the game board does not fill up completely,
as that would end the game.

  One fun thing about this otherwise useless game [What? Me?
Making a useless game? Naaah... ;) ] is that you get to see some of
the beautiful "home made" lightning bolts that are generated each
time you click on one of the, also home made, outstanding (!)
clouds.

  Have fun!

